Sometimes, a migration would fail when users are attempting an OnDemand migration from an Enterprise Hosting instance, with the following message:
{code}
Could not start the migration to [INSTANCE_NAME]
Could not perform import on OnDemand instance: java.net.SocketTimeoutException: Read timed out
{code}

This is caused by the size of the attachments, which exceeds 2GB.

Should this be possible in the first place? If you don't tick the "Create reciprocal link" checkbox when adding an application link, clicking "Create" results in a brief spinner and then nothing. These errors appear in the logs:

{code}
2012-11-01 14:33:25,510 TP-Processor10 WARN nmason 873x13891x1 1nbi2av 59.167.133.12,59.167.133.70 /rest/applinks/1.0/applicationlinkForm/createAppLink [apache.commons.httpclient.HttpMethodDirector] Required proxy credentials not available for BASIC <any realm>@squid:3128
